comments: Caldwell-Pope (WAS) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Green (HOU) and absorbs the contact.
Green (HOU) makes marginal contact with Neto's (WAS) body after the release that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) legally contests Wood's (HOU) jump shot attempt.
Green (HOU) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is taken.
Neto (WAS) moves laterally into Wood's (HOU) path and delivers body contact that affects Wood's FOM.
Avdija (WAS) makes clean contact with the ball before incidental contact occurs with Tate (HOU) as the ball is dislodged.
Both Caldwell-Pope (WAS) and Green (HOU) engage in incidental contact while pursuing the loose ball.
Caldwell-Pope (WAS) and Tate (HOU) make incidental contact as they collide during Caldwell-Pope's cut off-ball.
Wood (HOU) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
As Avdija (WAS) legally posts up, incidental contact occurs with Porter Jr. (HOU) in the lane.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the on-court ruling of goaltending is confirmed. Green (HOU) makes contact with the ball after it has made contact with the backboard.
Neto (WAS) legally contests Porter Jr.'s (HOU) jump shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that a clock malfunction had occurred and .04 seconds were put back on the clock.
